    <item>
      <title>Entity component system</title>
      <link>https://yantonov.com/post/2020-10-31-entity-component-system/</link>
      <guid>https://yantonov.com/post/2020-10-31-entity-component-system/</guid>
      <pubDate>Sat, 31 Oct 2020 13:09:03 +0500</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34;&gt;&lt;code&gt;Entity–component–system (ECS) is an architectural pattern that is mostly used in game development.
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;p&gt;Main points:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;every entity has unique id;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;every logic aspect is a component - raw data linked to the corresponding entity by id;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;system performs actions on entities having corresponding aspects/components;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;diffenent components can be stored separately;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;systems can track entities by using observer pattern.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;p&gt;More details can be found &lt;a href=&#34;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Entity_component_system&#34;&gt;here&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    
    <item>
      <title>About passing dependencies through deep call stack</title>
      <link>https://yantonov.com/post/2020-10-30-about-passing-dependencies-through-deep-call-stack/</link>
      <guid>https://yantonov.com/post/2020-10-30-about-passing-dependencies-through-deep-call-stack/</guid>
      <pubDate>Fri, 30 Oct 2020 19:23:06 +0500</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://github.com/dry-python/returns#requirescontext-container&#34;&gt;Here&lt;/a&gt; is another approach to pass dependencies through deep call stack.&lt;br&gt;
In a couple of words:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;deeply nested code not executes immediately but returns a function for the later lazy evaluation;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;the correponding function accepts the required environment;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;at the top level call the function returned from the nested code and pass the environment to it.
&lt;a href=&#34;https://returns.readthedocs.io/en/latest/pages/context.html&#34;&gt;Documentation&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;</description>
    </item>
    
