    <item>
      <title>Nice alternative to mocks, generate stub implementation</title>
      <link>https://yantonov.com/post/2020-08-27-nice-alternative-to-mocks-generate-stub-implementation/</link>
      <guid>https://yantonov.com/post/2020-08-27-nice-alternative-to-mocks-generate-stub-implementation/</guid>
      <pubDate>Thu, 27 Aug 2020 17:47:15 +0500</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://github.com/matryer/moq&#34;&gt;Here&lt;/a&gt; is nice &lt;a href=&#34;https://golang.org/&#34;&gt;go&lt;/a&gt; library named &amp;lsquo;moq&amp;rsquo; that helps you to easily test dependent code but without verbose mocks setup.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The idea is to generate trivial implementations and just save all the calls as a list preserving all the arguments.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Using this you can simply assert all the invariants and stop to write long mock setup.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    
